(187, 1, '2012-07-27 23:15:33', '2012-07-28 03:15:33', 'The Trinity of Carnatic music refer to the outstanding trio of composer-musicians of Carnatic music in the 18th century, being Tyāgarāja, Muthuswami Dikshitar and Syama Sastri. Prolific in composition, the Trinity of Carnatic music are known for creating a new era in the history of Carnatic music by bringing about a noticeable change in what was the existing Carnatic music tradition.[ Compositions of the Trinity of Carnatic music are recognised as being distinct in style, and original in handling ragas.', 'Slider Image 1', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'slider-image-1', '', '', '2012-09-19 22:30:59', '2012-09-20 02:30:59', '', 0, 'http://bramkaslp01/ragamalika/?page_id=187', 0, 'page', '', 0),
