(390, 1, '2012-07-01 23:17:46', '2012-07-02 03:17:46', '<p>Please find links to the necessary information you would need to become a prospective student of Ragamalika. If you have already been learning Classical music for some time now please let us know what you have learnt till date and From who?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The process of learning carnatic music can be divided into 3 parts</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Beginner- One who has to start from the basic lessons.</li>\r\n	<li>Intermediate- you have already learnt sarali Varisai,Janta varisai,Upper sthyai varisai alankaras, And geetams.</li>\r\n	<li>Advanced- Kritis,Keertanams,Ragam,neraval swar a Kalpanai and more.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Every new student is evaluated individually and then placed in an appropriate group by <span class="signature">Mrs. Maragatham</span>.</p>', 'New Student Info', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '10-revision-5', '', '', '2012-07-01 23:17:46', '2012-07-02 03:17:46', '', 10, 'http://bramkaslp01/ragamalika/10-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(287, 1, '2012-07-28 17:45:56', '2012-07-28 17:45:56', 'A Carnatic music association founded by Maragatham Ramaswamy\r\n\r\nCarnatic is the classical music of Southern India. It is based upon a complex system of ragam and talam. The melodic foundation is the ragam. Ragam is basically the scale. The seven notes of the scale are Sa, Ri, Ga, Ma, Pa, Dha, and Ni.\r\n\r\nRagamalika is a garland of Ragams.\r\n\r\nThis website has been built by the students of Ragamalika as a tribute to the works and teachings of Maragatham Ramaswamy.', 'About', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about', '', '', '2012-08-06 16:27:15', '2012-08-06 20:27:15', '', 0, 'http://bramkaslp01/ragamalika/?p=287', 0, 'page', '', 0),
