(151, 1, '2012-07-01 23:14:07', '2012-07-02 03:14:07', '<h3>Carnatic Music</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Carnatic music is the classical music of southern india which comprises of 4 states. Tamilnadu, AndraPradesh, Karnataka and Kerala. It is based on the 72 nomenclature system of ragas. The 72 ragas are called Janaka or parent Ragas. The ragas derived from these parent ragas are called Janya ragas or derived ragas.The basic elements of sruti (the relative musical pitch), swara (the musical sound of a single note), raga (the mode or melodic formula), and Tala (the rhythmic cycles) form the foundation of improvisation and composition in Carnatic music. Although improvisation plays an important role, Carnatic music is mainly sung through compositions, especially the kriti (or keertanams).The main emphasis in Carnatic music is on vocal music; most compositions are written to be sung, and even when played on instruments, they are meant to be performed in the singing style.Add the glossary from ragamalika.</p>\r\n', 'Carnatic Music', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '147-revision-3', '', '', '2012-07-01 23:14:07', '2012-07-02 03:14:07', '', 147, 'http://bramkaslp01/ragamalika/147-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(152, 1, '2012-06-25 01:33:49', '2012-06-25 05:33:49', 'Please find links to the necessary information you would need to become a prospective student of Ragamalika. If you have already been learning Classical music for some time now please let us know what you have learnt till date and From who?\r\n\r\nThe process of learning carnatic music can be divided into 3 parts\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Beginner- One who has to start from the basic lessons.</li>\r\n	<li>Intermediate- you have already learnt sarali Varisai,Janta varisai,Upper sthyai varisai alankaras, And geetams.</li>\r\n	<li>Advanced- Kritis,Keertanams,Ragam,neraval swar a Kalpanai and more.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nEvery new student is evaluated individually and then placed in an appropriate group by Mrs.Maragatham.', 'New Student Info', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '10-revision-4', '', '', '2012-06-25 01:33:49', '2012-06-25 05:33:49', '', 10, 'http://bramkaslp01/ragamalika/10-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
